      "timestep_posted": 41
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "Available is a driver-focused 2008 BMW M3 (E92) featuring the high-revving S65 4.0L V8 powerplant. This naturally aspirated engine utilizes individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing to achieve a stratospheric 8,400 RPM redline. To address common platform concerns, the rod bearings have been replaced with treated shells and the throttle actuators have been upgraded, ensuring long-term mechanical reliability. The 6-speed manual transmission provides tactile engagement, paired with the M-Variable Differential Lock for precise torque distribution across the rear axle. The chassis remains composed thanks to the Electronic Damper Control (EDC) system, offering adjustable damping rates to suit various road conditions. While the exterior shows minor stone chipping and interior bolsters exhibit typical wear, the subframe is structurally sound and the drivetrain remains leak-free. A mechanically sorted example ready for the apex.",
